deck: Marilyn Seong is a Korean-American woman in her early twenties with ALS. By the use of technology invented by herself, she has become the superhero Mecha Maid.
description:
When Marilyn was 13, she was diagnosed with ALS, and has since been on wheelchair. Trying to fight the disease, she began studying robot-technology. She managed to created an amplifier to enhance her nerves, and thereby make her body work normally. But it also unexpectedly granted her superhuman strength. But she still had ALS, and was destined to die young. Knowing that her tech would be used as a weapon instead of helping others with the same decease as her, Marilyn dedicated her life to helping others in the short time she had left. She created the superhero identity Mecha Maid based on Mahoromatic, her favorite anime, and started to fight crime and help others as best she could.

She made partnership with Tiger, and later a rocky-hero named Spinnerette. Spinnerette and Mecha Maid became very good friend, and Mecha Maid soon fell in love with her. But not having the nerves to confess, she settles with being Spinnerette's friend.

After an accident during a heavy storm, her suit was damaged, and Spinnerette had to carry her to the hospital, since she was unable to move. In the hospital-bed, Mecha Maid found the courage to confess her feelings to Spinnerette. The result was that Spinnerette ran out of the room, which hurt Mecha Maid's feelings. After this came a long and awkward week, where Mecha Maid acted like nothing had happened, claiming that she was to drugged up to know what she said in the hospital. It ended with a drunk Spinnerette entering Mecha Maid's lab at the middle of the night, and started to strip herself naked in order to seduce her. Mecha Maid reacted angrily to Spinnerette's assumption that sex and love meant the same thing, but after Spinnerette collapse and explains how scared she was, since this was the first time anyone had ever told her that they were in love with her, Mecha Maid forgives her, and they start dating.

Powers & Abilities

Mecha Maid has superhuman strength from her maid headband that manipulates her muscles. She also wears armor which provides her with several weapons and grant her flight.

She possess a genius level IQ, able to build her armor and an advanced AI system that serves her in her lab.
name: Mecha Maid

deck: James Gordon's mysterious cellmate in Blackgate Prison and former gangland of Gotham known as the Lion. Father of Catwoman
description:
Rex Calabrese was a crime boss who dominated the Gotham underworld decades ago. His scarred face and use of fake razor sharp fangs earned him the alias the Lion, a persona which helped him rise to prominence in the mob during a time before criminals wore costumes, masks or face paint. Calabrese believed that there was a Natural Order to crime and that one day, much like he had done to the previous mob boss, an up and coming gangster would depose and kill him. It was rumored that Carmine Falcone fulfilled this prophecy, but while Calabrese lost control of the underworld to Falcone, he was not killed but instead incarcerated in Black Gate prison.

Years later, Jim Gordon was jailed for his role in a subway crash and ended up sharing a cell with Calabrese. During a prison riot both men worked together to maintain order and minimize death. After the riot, Selina Kyle broke into Black Gate to meet with the Lion and during their discussion he encouraged her to seize power and unify the crime families under her leadership.
name: Rex Calabrese

deck: Brother of Alice Liddle. He became the second Mad Hatter in Wonderland.
description:
Origin

The second Mad Hatter, from the late 20th century. Drake was a fireman, husband, and seemingly loving uncle from Los Angeles. Secretly however, he molested his nephew Johnny on fishing expeditions alone with the boy. After one of these excursions Johnny confessed his uncle's crime to his grandfather (Charles Dodgson). That night when Drake went visit his father, Charles accused him of pedophilia and thrust him through the mirror into Wonderland.

In Wonderland, Drake found himself trapped between the March Hare and a wall of undead corpses. He was grabbed by the wall and bargained with the hare for his aid. The hare freed him from the wall and in exchange he offered him the 10/6 hat and sends him on a quest to fetch a girl named Lacie. Drake then wandered the jungle for months, becoming exhausted, and ever more insane. He came across a mirror and there, speaking with his reflection, finally gave up and gave in to Wonderland. In doing so he was able to don the mantle of the Mad Hatter and inherited all of the previous Hatter's skin suits. Months later he returned to March Hare and the tea party with Lacie and declared himself leader of the little group.

Major Story Arcs

Return To Wonderland

Years later, when Calie arrived in Wonderland, she fled the Cheshire Cat and ended up at Drake's door. He answers in a handsome disguise, offering her hospice. But instead of safety he deceived, drugged, and then attempted to rape her. She escaped and thoroughly beat him.

Beyond Wonderland

Trapped in Wonderland, Johnny Liddle wandered around a little. Disguised as the Mad Hatter, Drake Liddle knocked out Johnny after a brief conversation and distraction. Drake put Johnny in his dungeon together with Alice Liddle. Upon realizing who the Mad Hatter really was, Johnny broke free from his shackles and suffocated Drake with them. Forced to kill his mother with the Ebony Blade, Johnny uses it on a taunting Drake Liddle, thus killing him.
name: Drake Liddle

deck: Glass is a sadist and insane. He enjoy cutting flesh more than anything, and the only thing that makes him have any type of restrain is his loyalty to North Korea.
description:
Colonel Glass works for North Korea as a soldier, and is infamous for his ability to telepathically control glass. In 1985, during a exchange of prisoners, Glass was the represent North Korea. In ended up in conflict, when Glass refused to let one of the prisoners leave with her child, and he decided to cut up and kill the baby. This made South Korea's represent, the hero White Heron, attack Glass in a attempt to save the infant, which started a fight between the two of them, ending with Heron sacrificing her own life to save the child.

Years later, Glass was sent to America to get steal a Kirby Reactor.

Powers & Abilities

Colonel Glass has telepathic control over glass, and can manipulate it as he please. He can make it float in air, and move it with incredible speed. He can move thousands of glass pieces with ease, and has a huge range.

He also has regeneration, and can regrow an arm on mere seconds.
name: Colonel Glass

deck: Empowered by the "Spirit Of The Tiger," Jeff Coleman is NOT a black superhero, but a superhero who happens to be black.
description:
Jeff Coleman was a normal policeman until the day he found an elderly superhero who had been shot. Knowing that he was dying, the old man transferred his "Spirit Of The Tiger" powers to Jeff. Jeff then became the superhero Tiger, but was commonly known as Black Tiger, much to his annoyance, since he didn't want his identity to be a race-thing.

One night, his wife caught him changing into his Tiger costume, and his secret was exposed to her. Upset, she threatened to leave Jeff if he continued being Tiger, since she thought is was unfair to their children if he took such a unnecessary risk. Despite Jeff's two daughter joy over having a superhero as dad, Jeff promised his wife to burn the costume, and make sure that his daughters wouldn't end up fatherless.

Jeff stopped using his powers and returned to being a normal police officer. But one day, after coming home from work, he learned that there was a shooting at his daughters' school. His girls were okay, but he realized that all the children would have been saved, if he was still Tiger. His wife left him with their children, and Jeff focused on being as good a superhero as possible for his children's sake.

Some years later, Jeff became very passionate(possibly obsessed) about his superhero-identity, and made sure to lift weight several hours a day and drink 200 grams of protein in milkshakes in order to stay in shape. He was the partner of the hero known as Thunderfist for a long time, until Thunderfist decided to work for the government as Agent 7.

Tiger eventually formed a superhero trio with Mecha Maid and Spinnerette, for whom he was a sort of mentor for.

Powers & Abilities

Tiger is empowered by the "Spirit Of The Tiger," which grant him superhuman strength. He can also summon the spirit outside his body, and make it attack his opponents.

He is a policeman, and therefor has all the training and education, which mean he is, among many things; a skilled hand-to-hand fighter, and also a pretty sharp detective.

Tiger is in his forties, but is in splendid shape duo to several hours of weightlifting, a ton of chicken-breast, and several protein-milkshakes.
name: Tiger

deck: A sharpshooter from Arkansas hired by Joe Malizia to kill the Punisher.
description:
Punisher Welcome Back, Frank

Harry "Heck" Thornton is a redneck from Arkansas and a sharp shooter hired by Joe Malizia, Ma Gnuuci's right hand man. Harry along with a few other hired mercenaries were contracted to kill the Punisher but none of them succeeded.

The Punisher (2004 Film)

Harry "Heck" Thornton is played by Mark Collie. In this adaption, Harry Heck is from Memphis rather than Arkansas. After a night of dealing with Joan's abusive boyfriend and setting up the Saints for their own demise, Frank goes downstairs for some coffee the next morning. Frank sits with the other tenants from his apartment building when all of a sudden, a new patron comes into Joan's Diner. Harry "Heck" Thornton has been hired by Howard Saint to take out Frank. Harry introduces himself by playing a swan song that he wrote especially for Frank. Afterwards, Harry tells Frank that he will be singing this sour tune at his funeral.

Frank takes his armored GTO for a ride in order to lure out Harry. Harry opens fire with a grenade launcher in order to pierce the armored car. Frank manages to get away but he is forced to swerve his car when a kid runs into the middle of the road. Frank's car flips and Frank crawls out from the wreckage. Harry walks up to Frank with 357 Magnum and Frank points a switchblade at Harry. Harry scoffs at Frank's supposed desperation and takes aim. Frank hits the trigger on the hilt and the switchblade shoots out into Harry's neck. Harry chokes on his own blood as he falls to the ground.
name: Harry Thornton
